    "summary": "Matteo Luppi is a researcher at the Centre for Social Policy and Intervention Studies (SOPINS). He obtained his European PhD in Socio-Economic and Statistical Studies (Euro PhD SESS) at the Sapienza University of Rome, on a study on the relation between poverty and dependency condition. His research interests include Comparative studies of welfare states (Long Term Care sector), poverty, social inequality and intergenerational inequality.\nHis current research focus on the ageing process of the European population and its consequences at family, individual and national level. The research purpose is to understand how the two opposite forces of welfare budget constraints and increasing care demand, affect the socio-economic condition of the individuals involved in this process: dependent elderly, family caregivers and care workers. At UU Matteo participates in the project Balancing Gender and Generational Citizenship (WP9) within the FP7 research program bEUcitizen.\n",
